## Danger Zone

### Leaving the Team

Non-owner members can leave the team:

1. Navigate to the Danger Zone section
1. Click **Leave Team**
1. Type "LEAVE" in the confirmation field
1. Click **Confirm**

After leaving:

- You lose access to the team immediately
- Your content remains with the team
- You can be invited back later

> **Note:** Primary owners cannot leave a team. Transfer ownership first if you need to leave.

### Deleting the Team

Primary owners can delete the entire team:

1. Navigate to Danger Zone
1. Click **Delete Team**
1. Read the warning
1. Complete OTP verification (a 6-digit code will be sent to your email)
1. Enter the code and confirm deletion

> **Warning:** Deleting a team permanently removes all data including:
> 
> - All team members

- All campaigns
- All leads and interactions
- All sales and commission data
- All configuration

This action cannot be undone.

## Saving Changes

Changes to team settings are saved when you click the **Update Team** button. You'll see a confirmation notification when changes are saved successfully.

## Troubleshooting

### Can't Access Settings

If you can't access settings:

1. Check your role in the Members page
1. Contact your team owner

### Changes Not Saving

If changes don't save:

1. Check for validation error messages
1. Verify all required fields are filled
1. Check your internet connection
1. Try refreshing the page

### Logo Won't Upload

If logo upload fails:

1. Check file size (must be under the limit)
1. Verify file format (JPG, PNG supported)
1. Try a different image
1. Clear browser cache

### Can't Delete Team

If you can't delete the team:

1. Verify you are the primary owner
1. Check if the feature is enabled for your organization
1. Complete the OTP verification correctly

